        <SPEC-OBJECT IDENTIFIER="id-17cf55a80941c033e217c1b9bc517a9c" LAST-CHANGE="2023-04-17T14:14:08.073-04:00" LONG-NAME="9317262aa7fe1561944d8534c5610a39d2ab3936e668051302ee8a7624265243">
          <VALUES>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="9317262aa7fe1561944d8534c5610a39d2ab3936e668051302ee8a7624265243">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-474bf8df001703d4f13bcf6621ec60e3</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-XHTML>
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-XHTML-REF>id-356fa0b261512705956dc6124b01c001</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-XHTML-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
              <THE-VALUE>
                <xhtml:div>
<xhtml:div>
<xhtml:p>
<xhtml:strong>The user of MICROSAR Safe shall enable plausibility checks for the MICROSAR Safe components.</xhtml:strong>
</xhtml:p>
<xhtml:p>
This setting is necessary to introduce defensive programming and increase robustness at the interfaces as required by ISO 26262.
<xhtml:br/>
This setting shall be configured at /MICROSAR/EcuC/EcucGeneral/EcuCSafeBswChecks <xhtml:strong>and</xhtml:strong> &lt;Component-specific path>/&lt;Ma>SafeBswChecks for all components that are intended to be ASIL.
<xhtml:br/>
<xhtml:em>Ma</xhtml:em> is the Module Abbreviation.
<xhtml:br/>
This setting is enforced by an MSSV plug-in.
<xhtml:br/>
This setting does not enable error reporting to the DET component.
</xhtml:p>
</xhtml:div>
</xhtml:div>
              </THE-VALUE>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-XHTML>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="SMI-18">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-916bfa90513366b6033b4ebb05e88b13</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="SMI-68A3554E-18AF-4DE8-B9AD-169BBAD0959F">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-f71c12daf9754c5c0ec9549bb0a19b12</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
