        <SPEC-OBJECT IDENTIFIER="id-31d4ceb3eed860166e8f099f59a729db" LAST-CHANGE="2023-04-17T14:14:08.073-04:00" LONG-NAME="3750cb93cf59cc79023cad61992304518708e6bb511ce38a503883b0a5ebaa20">
          <VALUES>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="3750cb93cf59cc79023cad61992304518708e6bb511ce38a503883b0a5ebaa20">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-474bf8df001703d4f13bcf6621ec60e3</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-XHTML>
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-XHTML-REF>id-356fa0b261512705956dc6124b01c001</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-XHTML-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
              <THE-VALUE>
                <xhtml:div>
<xhtml:div>
<xhtml:p>
<xhtml:strong>The user of MICROSAR Safe shall verify that the memory mapping is consistent with the partitioning concept.</xhtml:strong>
<xhtml:br/>
The volatile data of every component shall be placed in the associated memory partition. This can be verified e.g. by review of the linker map file.
<xhtml:br/>
The memory sections for each component placed in RAM can be identified &lt;MIP>_START_SEC_VAR[_&lt;xxx>], where &lt;MIP> is the Module Implementation Prefix of the component.
<xhtml:br/>
It is assumed that the MPU is configured to not allow write access by a partition with lower integrity to data from a partition with higher integrity.
</xhtml:p>
</xhtml:div>
</xhtml:div>
              </THE-VALUE>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-XHTML>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="SMI-99">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-916bfa90513366b6033b4ebb05e88b13</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
