        <SPEC-OBJECT IDENTIFIER="id-48ffcdc7a8b15143af712e42923df480" LAST-CHANGE="2023-04-17T14:14:08.073-04:00" LONG-NAME="f5509e2877362953edddf65dbb1001d71f03d1b74903205a458fb6c368de82c9">
          <VALUES>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="f5509e2877362953edddf65dbb1001d71f03d1b74903205a458fb6c368de82c9">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-474bf8df001703d4f13bcf6621ec60e3</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-XHTML>
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-XHTML-REF>id-356fa0b261512705956dc6124b01c001</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-XHTML-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
              <THE-VALUE>
                <xhtml:div>
<xhtml:div>
<xhtml:p>
<xhtml:strong>The user of MICROSAR Safe shall provide sufficient resources in RAM, ROM, stack and CPU runtime for MICROSAR Safe.</xhtml:strong>
</xhtml:p>
<xhtml:p>
Selection of the microcontroller and memory capacities as well as dimensioning of the stacks is in the responsibility of the user of MICROSAR Safe.
<xhtml:br/>
If MICROSAR Safe components have specific requirements, these are documented in the respective Technical Reference document.
</xhtml:p>
</xhtml:div>
</xhtml:div>
              </THE-VALUE>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-XHTML>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="SMI-33">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-916bfa90513366b6033b4ebb05e88b13</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING>
