        <SPEC-OBJECT IDENTIFIER="id-8e2abf6e49fbe93bcef83cb812b2c6c8" LAST-CHANGE="2023-04-17T14:14:08.073-04:00" LONG-NAME="0cdd3a53d7583fbdb226eaea95cc24ed8b84ea37fcd78025813baf4589e664e2">
          <VALUES>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="0cdd3a53d7583fbdb226eaea95cc24ed8b84ea37fcd78025813baf4589e664e2">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-474bf8df001703d4f13bcf6621ec60e3</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-XHTML>
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-XHTML-REF>id-356fa0b261512705956dc6124b01c001</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-XHTML-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
              <THE-VALUE>
                <xhtml:div>
<xhtml:div>
<xhtml:p>The user of MICROSAR Safe shall verify that the CRC is calculated for the intended data.</xhtml:p>
<xhtml:p>
This includes the intended buffer and its size (see also SMI-16), start value and if it is the first call to the service.
<xhtml:br/>
Verification can be performed by the &quot;magic check&quot; (see AUTOSAR SWS Crc).
</xhtml:p>
<xhtml:p>If Crc is used by a MICROSAR Safe component (e.g. E2E, NvM), this requirement is fulfilled for the MICROSAR Safe component.</xhtml:p>
</xhtml:div>
</xhtml:div>
              </THE-VALUE>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-XHTML>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="SMI-49">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-916bfa90513366b6033b4ebb05e88b13</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING>
