        <SPEC-OBJECT IDENTIFIER="id-b1417d360d50b58dfa8f2d6f417f4944" LAST-CHANGE="2023-04-17T14:14:08.073-04:00" LONG-NAME="47ed8938f9977969917fe4858b8736e10921856e95dabcc192c555005f736ae2">
          <VALUES>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="47ed8938f9977969917fe4858b8736e10921856e95dabcc192c555005f736ae2">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-474bf8df001703d4f13bcf6621ec60e3</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-XHTML>
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-XHTML-REF>id-356fa0b261512705956dc6124b01c001</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-XHTML-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
              <THE-VALUE>
                <xhtml:div>
<xhtml:div>
<xhtml:p>
The user of MICROSAR Safe shall verify that the E2E library communication states are not modified by the application while an E2EPW API function is running.
<xhtml:br/>
If a pointer to the senders/receivers E2E library communication state is required, it shall be queried with <xhtml:em>E2EPW_GetProtectState_p_o()</xhtml:em> / <xhtml:em>E2EPW_GetCheckState_p_o()</xhtml:em>.
<xhtml:br/>
Make sure that the values of the E2E library communication state are only read and not altered by the application or a module other than the E2EPW or the E2E library unless intended so.
<xhtml:br/>
For special purposes, modification of the sequence counter by the application may be useful or required. Be aware that this is done in the responsibility of the user of MICROSAR Safe.
</xhtml:p>
</xhtml:div>
</xhtml:div>
              </THE-VALUE>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-XHTML>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="SMI-136">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-916bfa90513366b6033b4ebb05e88b13</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="SMI-FEA226CE-FAF6-4C51-B19F-E55947D79491">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-f71c12daf9754c5c0ec9549bb0a19b12</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING>
