        <SPEC-OBJECT IDENTIFIER="id-8e4a52718bb68380916c4425ce657dd8" LAST-CHANGE="2023-04-17T14:14:08.073-04:00" LONG-NAME="8e18462a65de45930ccb0bb639073c91bd60266df91f355e88f00280fad183a6">
          <VALUES>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="8e18462a65de45930ccb0bb639073c91bd60266df91f355e88f00280fad183a6">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-474bf8df001703d4f13bcf6621ec60e3</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-XHTML>
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-XHTML-REF>id-356fa0b261512705956dc6124b01c001</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-XHTML-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
              <THE-VALUE>
                <xhtml:div>
<xhtml:div>
<xhtml:p>The user of MICROSAR Safe shall verify that all APIs called in ISRs of category 0 are allowed to be called in this context by the technical reference.</xhtml:p>
<xhtml:p>The call context „inside category 0 ISR“ cannot be checked by the API functions. Erroneous calls are not detected.</xhtml:p>
</xhtml:div>
</xhtml:div>
              </THE-VALUE>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-XHTML>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="SMI-44677">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-916bfa90513366b6033b4ebb05e88b13</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING>
