        <SPEC-OBJECT IDENTIFIER="id-25490f314598ccefd914f53145fc1a21" LAST-CHANGE="2023-04-17T14:14:08.073-04:00" LONG-NAME="f95920c8fbfcd17d4c5c3a68b09df47bd228998c130934aab199a1e381ff7a52">
          <VALUES>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="f95920c8fbfcd17d4c5c3a68b09df47bd228998c130934aab199a1e381ff7a52">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-474bf8df001703d4f13bcf6621ec60e3</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-XHTML>
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-XHTML-REF>id-356fa0b261512705956dc6124b01c001</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-XHTML-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
              <THE-VALUE>
                <xhtml:div>
<xhtml:div>
<xhtml:p>
The user of MICROSAR Safe shall avoid forcible termination by means of the protection reaction of the <xhtml:em>ProtectionHook</xhtml:em> in case category 0 ISRs are configured.
</xhtml:p>
<xhtml:p>
If a category 0 ISR causes the <xhtml:em>ProtectionHook</xhtml:em> call, the interrupted Task or ISR would be terminated together with the category 0 ISR.
<xhtml:br/>
This situation should be handled safely in the application design.
</xhtml:p>
</xhtml:div>
</xhtml:div>
              </THE-VALUE>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-XHTML>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="SMI-44675">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-916bfa90513366b6033b4ebb05e88b13</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="SMI-18B0D655-947B-446E-B7BC-98CA62F93CDE">
              <DEFINITION>
