        <SPEC-OBJECT IDENTIFIER="id-052d5ac29a7124b0246b3492ee699073" LAST-CHANGE="2023-04-17T14:14:08.073-04:00" LONG-NAME="b7a0ff336d8378d3b55c7f75088d5896107ff58a45d0ec805eed5a7db4cac6f6">
          <VALUES>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="b7a0ff336d8378d3b55c7f75088d5896107ff58a45d0ec805eed5a7db4cac6f6">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-474bf8df001703d4f13bcf6621ec60e3</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-XHTML>
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-XHTML-REF>id-356fa0b261512705956dc6124b01c001</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-XHTML-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
              <THE-VALUE>
                <xhtml:div>
<xhtml:div>
<xhtml:p>
The user of MICROSAR Safe shall verify the configuration of access rights to sections.
<xhtml:br/>
A precondition to this is, that a concept exists, which describes the partitioning of the address range and the access rights to the partitions for different parts of the software.
</xhtml:p>
<xhtml:p>This can be done by stopping the execution and checking the MPU register values. Dependent on the granularity of the access right configuration, this should be done globally (static MPU regions), for each OS Application or for each Task and each ISR.</xhtml:p>
</xhtml:div>
</xhtml:div>
              </THE-VALUE>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-XHTML>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="SMI-564">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-916bfa90513366b6033b4ebb05e88b13</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="SMI-EAFE55DB-E72D-4F0D-A949-9E65812F8F3F">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-f71c12daf9754c5c0ec9549bb0a19b12</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="RQM_SAFETY_MANUAL_ITEM">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-83df1902a3d82b5ad802413febd9486c</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING>
