        <SPEC-OBJECT IDENTIFIER="id-5f27c1db2d14942affdbef24a176580e" LAST-CHANGE="2023-04-17T14:14:08.073-04:00" LONG-NAME="42de3ae2c06094828d17f3661d66ca24aded99e8603bb554f349a03fb0b9a209">
          <VALUES>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="42de3ae2c06094828d17f3661d66ca24aded99e8603bb554f349a03fb0b9a209">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-474bf8df001703d4f13bcf6621ec60e3</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-XHTML>
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-XHTML-REF>id-356fa0b261512705956dc6124b01c001</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-XHTML-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
              <THE-VALUE>
                <xhtml:div>
<xhtml:div>
<xhtml:p>
The user of MICROSAR Safe shall not rely on the error parameter macros.
<xhtml:br/>
These are named: OSError_&lt;API-name>_&lt;parameter-name>().
<xhtml:br/>
They are not assumed as safety requirements by Vector.
</xhtml:p>
</xhtml:div>
</xhtml:div>
              </THE-VALUE>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-XHTML>
