              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-DATE-REF>id-1deeefdd91604feff8470574ac6fef3d</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-DATE-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-DATE>
          </VALUES>
          <TYPE>
            <SPEC-OBJECT-TYPE-REF>id-9005dd4fc53fa9c4b4bcb1b9bddbb116</SPEC-OBJECT-TYPE-REF>
          </TYPE>
        </SPEC-OBJECT>
        <SPEC-OBJECT IDENTIFIER="id-8394f5efb20cd48ab5149338949e9369" LAST-CHANGE="2023-04-17T14:14:08.073-04:00" LONG-NAME="f94039dac3ae33f0d81bbf4d88fc7a554162f3b0f227f9aedc340fd55aee060f">
          <VALUES>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="f94039dac3ae33f0d81bbf4d88fc7a554162f3b0f227f9aedc340fd55aee060f">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-474bf8df001703d4f13bcf6621ec60e3</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-XHTML>
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-XHTML-REF>id-356fa0b261512705956dc6124b01c001</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-XHTML-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
              <THE-VALUE>
                <xhtml:div>
<xhtml:div>
<xhtml:p>The user of MICROSAR Safe shall verify that the type Os_AppAccessMaskType is generated in accordance to the number of configured OS Applications and that OS_APPMASK_BITWIDTH is defined in accordance to the processors bit width. </xhtml:p>
<xhtml:p>
The definition for OS_APPMASK_BITWIDTH may be found in Os_Application_Lcfg.h:
<xhtml:br/>
#define OS_APPMASK_BITWIDTH        (&lt;BitWidth>u)
</xhtml:p>
<xhtml:p>The type definition for AppAccessMaskType may be found in Os_Types_Lcfg.h.</xhtml:p>
<xhtml:p>If OS_APPID_COUNT is larger than &lt;BitWidth>:</xhtml:p>
<xhtml:p>typedef P2CONST(uint&lt;BitWidth>, TYPEDEF, OS_CONST)  Os_AppAccessMaskType;</xhtml:p>
<xhtml:p>Otherwise:</xhtml:p>
<xhtml:p>typedef uint&lt;BitWidth>  Os_AppAccessMaskType;</xhtml:p>
<xhtml:p>Where &lt;BitWidth> is the bit width of the processor (32 or 64).</xhtml:p>
</xhtml:div>
</xhtml:div>
              </THE-VALUE>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-XHTML>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="SMI-429122">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-916bfa90513366b6033b4ebb05e88b13</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="SMI-69E26772-DAF4-47F5-A081-F5E265470C62">
              <DEFINITION>
