        <SPEC-OBJECT IDENTIFIER="id-be5caa5f77d11dad0e55906d9b7f4102" LAST-CHANGE="2023-04-17T14:14:08.073-04:00" LONG-NAME="7d5ea19c867bbf327de5899f45e9f27de790be1c20c35569a4d368aff9f88615">
          <VALUES>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="7d5ea19c867bbf327de5899f45e9f27de790be1c20c35569a4d368aff9f88615">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-474bf8df001703d4f13bcf6621ec60e3</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-XHTML>
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-XHTML-REF>id-cccf5234afd68596b1e3e3f55dea2015</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-XHTML-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
              <THE-VALUE>
                <xhtml:div>
<xhtml:div>
<xhtml:p>Inter OS Application Communication (IOC)</xhtml:p>
</xhtml:div>
</xhtml:div>
              </THE-VALUE>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-XHTML>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="9.3.9">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-5cc4ddac421a59e2d94cd9af3cb22413</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="DocItem">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-83df1902a3d82b5ad802413febd9486c</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-DATE THE-VALUE="2023-04-17T14:14:08.073-04:00">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-DATE-REF>id-aa6269f32be4c61f516adebdbf3b1e19</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-DATE-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-DATE>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-DATE THE-VALUE="2023-04-17T14:14:08.073-04:00">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-DATE-REF>id-1deeefdd91604feff8470574ac6fef3d</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-DATE-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-DATE>
          </VALUES>
          <TYPE>
            <SPEC-OBJECT-TYPE-REF>id-9005dd4fc53fa9c4b4bcb1b9bddbb116</SPEC-OBJECT-TYPE-REF>
          </TYPE>
        </SPEC-OBJECT>
        <SPEC-OBJECT IDENTIFIER="id-47295b759bb976b000d5b1c3ae2acd82" LAST-CHANGE="2023-04-17T14:14:08.073-04:00" LONG-NAME="131353945dd18ada192b16ef00928db86e8b633f84810e163f6dd175c7f27092">
          <VALUES>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="131353945dd18ada192b16ef00928db86e8b633f84810e163f6dd175c7f27092">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-474bf8df001703d4f13bcf6621ec60e3</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-XHTML>
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-XHTML-REF>id-356fa0b261512705956dc6124b01c001</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-XHTML-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
              <THE-VALUE>
                <xhtml:div>
<xhtml:div>
<xhtml:p>This chapter describes the review of the correctness of the locking mode generation in file Os_Ioc_Lcfg.c for all configured senders, writers, receivers and readers of IOC communications. In order to keep each safety manual item sufficiently simple, the review has been split into several items. However, it may make sense, to scan through the file for any sender, writer, receiver or reader configuration structures and to perform the respective review on them. Typically two safety manual items will describe the complete review for a specific sender, writer, receiver or reader. For the receivers of queued IOC communications, only one safety manual item needs to be considered.</xhtml:p>
</xhtml:div>
</xhtml:div>
              </THE-VALUE>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-XHTML>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="DocItem">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-83df1902a3d82b5ad802413febd9486c</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-DATE THE-VALUE="2023-04-17T14:14:08.073-04:00">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-DATE-REF>id-aa6269f32be4c61f516adebdbf3b1e19</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-DATE-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-DATE>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-DATE THE-VALUE="2023-04-17T14:14:08.073-04:00">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-DATE-REF>id-1deeefdd91604feff8470574ac6fef3d</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-DATE-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-DATE>
          </VALUES>
          <TYPE>
            <SPEC-OBJECT-TYPE-REF>id-9005dd4fc53fa9c4b4bcb1b9bddbb116</SPEC-OBJECT-TYPE-REF>
          </TYPE>
        </SPEC-OBJECT>
        <SPEC-OBJECT IDENTIFIER="id-5d95ebf8d068be17b44a584fd151a8b3" LAST-CHANGE="2023-04-17T14:14:08.073-04:00" LONG-NAME="bcf702b1376ebd1d7583328b5e16f0aacf2c123bd917b7ef2ed7236cf7a9d935">
          <VALUES>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="bcf702b1376ebd1d7583328b5e16f0aacf2c123bd917b7ef2ed7236cf7a9d935">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-474bf8df001703d4f13bcf6621ec60e3</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-XHTML>
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-XHTML-REF>id-356fa0b261512705956dc6124b01c001</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-XHTML-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
              <THE-VALUE>
                <xhtml:div>
<xhtml:div>
<xhtml:p>The user of MICROSAR Safe shall verify the consistency of the LockMode and the Spinlock pointer for all generated configuration structures of readers on IOC communications. The configuration data structure of readers in  Os_Ioc_Lcfg.c looks like:</xhtml:p>
<xhtml:pre>
<xhtml:code>CONST(Os_IocReadConfigType, OS_CONST) OsCfg_IocRecv_&lt;NameOfIocCommunication> =
<xhtml:br/>
{
<xhtml:br/>
/* .Ioc      = */
<xhtml:br/>
{
<xhtml:br/>
/* .Spinlock              = */ &lt;SpinlockPointer>,
<xhtml:br/>
/* .LockMode              = */ &lt;LockModeValue>,
<xhtml:br/>
...
<xhtml:br/>
/* .AccessingApplications = */ OS_APPID2MASK(&lt;NameOfOsApplication>)
<xhtml:br/>
&lt;|OS_APPID2MASK(&lt;NameOfOsApplication>)>*
<xhtml:br/>
},
<xhtml:br/>
...
<xhtml:br/>
};
<xhtml:br/>
</xhtml:code>
</xhtml:pre>
<xhtml:p>Where &lt;NameOfIocCommunication> is the configured short name of a container with definition ref: /MICROSAR/Os/OsIoc/OsIocCommunication and &lt;NameOfOsApplication> is the short name of a configuration container, reffered to by the parameter: /MICROSAR/Os/OsIoc/OsIocCommunication/OsIocReceiverProperties/OsIocReceivingOsApplicationRef of the Ioc communication. The values at &lt;SpinlockPointer> and &lt;LockModeValue> shall be reviewed against the table for consistency:</xhtml:p>
<xhtml:table>
                      <xhtml:tbody>
                        <xhtml:tr>
                          <xhtml:th> &lt;LockModeValue> </xhtml:th>
                          <xhtml:th> &lt;SpinlockPointer> </xhtml:th>
                        </xhtml:tr>
                        <xhtml:tr>
                          <xhtml:td>OS_IOCLOCKMODE_NONE</xhtml:td>
                          <xhtml:td>NULL_PTR</xhtml:td>
                        </xhtml:tr>
                        <xhtml:tr>
                          <xhtml:td>OS_IOCLOCKMODE_INTERRUPTS</xhtml:td>
                          <xhtml:td>NULL_PTR</xhtml:td>
                        </xhtml:tr>
                        <xhtml:tr>
                          <xhtml:td>OS_IOCLOCKMODE_SPINLOCKS</xhtml:td>
                          <xhtml:td>&amp;OsCfg_Spinlock_IocSpinlock_&lt;NameOfIocCommunication></xhtml:td>
                        </xhtml:tr>
                        <xhtml:tr>
                          <xhtml:td>OS_IOCLOCKMODE_ALL</xhtml:td>
                          <xhtml:td>&amp;OsCfg_Spinlock_IocSpinlock_&lt;NameOfIocCommunication></xhtml:td>
                        </xhtml:tr>
                      </xhtml:tbody>
                    </xhtml:table>
</xhtml:div>
</xhtml:div>
              </THE-VALUE>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-XHTML>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="SMI-889322">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-916bfa90513366b6033b4ebb05e88b13</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="SMI-F7964846-C743-4751-BAF6-2B6C60EFB711">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-f71c12daf9754c5c0ec9549bb0a19b12</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="RQM_SAFETY_MANUAL_ITEM">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-83df1902a3d82b5ad802413febd9486c</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-DATE THE-VALUE="2023-04-17T14:14:08.073-04:00">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-DATE-REF>id-aa6269f32be4c61f516adebdbf3b1e19</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-DATE-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-DATE>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-DATE THE-VALUE="2023-04-17T14:14:08.073-04:00">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-DATE-REF>id-1deeefdd91604feff8470574ac6fef3d</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-DATE-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-DATE>
          </VALUES>
          <TYPE>
            <SPEC-OBJECT-TYPE-REF>id-9005dd4fc53fa9c4b4bcb1b9bddbb116</SPEC-OBJECT-TYPE-REF>
          </TYPE>
        </SPEC-OBJECT>
        <SPEC-OBJECT IDENTIFIER="id-aa824b19d6130ad977c341ed5846cc41" LAST-CHANGE="2023-04-17T14:14:08.073-04:00" LONG-NAME="cf8cc8f3638d1ce611281e2362d56d081d347820be39bb6e7b04704e19d9a0da">
          <VALUES>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="cf8cc8f3638d1ce611281e2362d56d081d347820be39bb6e7b04704e19d9a0da">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-474bf8df001703d4f13bcf6621ec60e3</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-XHTML>
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-XHTML-REF>id-356fa0b261512705956dc6124b01c001</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-XHTML-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
              <THE-VALUE>
                <xhtml:div>
<xhtml:div>
<xhtml:p>The user of MICROSAR Safe shall verify the consistency of the LockMode and the Spinlock pointer for all generated configuration structures of writers on IOC communications. The configuration structure of writers in Os_Ioc_Lcfg.c looks like:</xhtml:p>
<xhtml:pre>
<xhtml:code>CONST(Os_IocWriteConfigType, OS_CONST)
<xhtml:br/>
OsCfg_IocSend_&lt;NameOfIocCommunication>&lt;_&lt;OsIocSenderId>>? =
<xhtml:br/>
{
<xhtml:br/>
/* .Ioc       = */
<xhtml:br/>
{
<xhtml:br/>
/* .Spinlock              = */ &lt;SpinlockPointer>,
<xhtml:br/>
/* .LockMode              = */ &lt;LockModeValue>,
<xhtml:br/>
...
<xhtml:br/>
/* .AccessingApplications = */ OS_APPID2MASK(&lt;NameOfOsApplication>)
<xhtml:br/>
},
<xhtml:br/>
...
<xhtml:br/>
};
<xhtml:br/>
</xhtml:code>
</xhtml:pre>
<xhtml:p>Where &lt;NameOfIocCommunication> is the configured short name of a container with definition ref: /MICROSAR/Os/OsIoc/OsIocCommunication, &lt;NameOfOsApplication> is the short name of a configuration container, reffered to by the parameter: /MICROSAR/Os/OsIoc/OsIocCommunication/OsIocSenderProperties/OsIocSendingOsApplicationRef and &lt;_&lt;OsIocSenderId>>? is the value of a parameter with definition ref: /MICROSAR/Os/OsIoc/OsIocCommunication/OsIocSenderProperties/OsIocSenderId of that IOC communication. This part of the name may not be available in 1:1 communication as the parameter needs not be configured then. The values at &lt;SpinlockPointer> and &lt;LockModeValue> shall be reviewed against the table for consistency:</xhtml:p>
<xhtml:table>
                      <xhtml:tbody>
                        <xhtml:tr>
                          <xhtml:th> &lt;LockModeValue> </xhtml:th>
                          <xhtml:th> &lt;SpinlockPointer> </xhtml:th>
                        </xhtml:tr>
                        <xhtml:tr>
                          <xhtml:td>OS_IOCLOCKMODE_NONE</xhtml:td>
                          <xhtml:td>NULL_PTR</xhtml:td>
                        </xhtml:tr>
                        <xhtml:tr>
                          <xhtml:td>OS_IOCLOCKMODE_INTERRUPTS</xhtml:td>
                          <xhtml:td>NULL_PTR</xhtml:td>
                        </xhtml:tr>
                        <xhtml:tr>
                          <xhtml:td>OS_IOCLOCKMODE_SPINLOCKS</xhtml:td>
                          <xhtml:td>&amp;OsCfg_Spinlock_IocSpinlock_&lt;NameOfIocCommunication></xhtml:td>
                        </xhtml:tr>
                        <xhtml:tr>
                          <xhtml:td>OS_IOCLOCKMODE_ALL</xhtml:td>
                          <xhtml:td>&amp;OsCfg_Spinlock_IocSpinlock_&lt;NameOfIocCommunication></xhtml:td>
                        </xhtml:tr>
                      </xhtml:tbody>
                    </xhtml:table>
</xhtml:div>
</xhtml:div>
              </THE-VALUE>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-XHTML>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="SMI-889323">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-916bfa90513366b6033b4ebb05e88b13</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="SMI-BC184977-3476-485C-A406-306FFB700A7B">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-f71c12daf9754c5c0ec9549bb0a19b12</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="RQM_SAFETY_MANUAL_ITEM">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-83df1902a3d82b5ad802413febd9486c</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-DATE THE-VALUE="2023-04-17T14:14:08.073-04:00">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-DATE-REF>id-aa6269f32be4c61f516adebdbf3b1e19</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-DATE-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-DATE>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-DATE THE-VALUE="2023-04-17T14:14:08.073-04:00">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-DATE-REF>id-1deeefdd91604feff8470574ac6fef3d</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-DATE-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-DATE>
          </VALUES>
          <TYPE>
            <SPEC-OBJECT-TYPE-REF>id-9005dd4fc53fa9c4b4bcb1b9bddbb116</SPEC-OBJECT-TYPE-REF>
          </TYPE>
        </SPEC-OBJECT>
        <SPEC-OBJECT IDENTIFIER="id-d993f58a0564eef5f3a7ce750077a22e" LAST-CHANGE="2023-04-17T14:14:08.073-04:00" LONG-NAME="2ce69baa12bd7e702effa46ea6635e3ff3cc0890dec4b69d40b1ecf3f55cca61">
          <VALUES>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="2ce69baa12bd7e702effa46ea6635e3ff3cc0890dec4b69d40b1ecf3f55cca61">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-474bf8df001703d4f13bcf6621ec60e3</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-XHTML>
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-XHTML-REF>id-356fa0b261512705956dc6124b01c001</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-XHTML-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
              <THE-VALUE>
                <xhtml:div>
<xhtml:div>
<xhtml:p>The user of MICROSAR Safe shall verify the correct generation of the LockMode for all readers and writers of a specific IOC communication. See SMI-889322 and SMI-889323 for the relevant configuration structures. The value for &lt;LockMode> shall be identical for all readers and writers and be in accordance to the table:</xhtml:p>
<xhtml:table>
                      <xhtml:tbody>
                        <xhtml:tr>
                          <xhtml:th>Data can be read/written atomically</xhtml:th>
                          <xhtml:th>Core local and/or Cross-Core communication</xhtml:th>
                          <xhtml:th>&lt;LockMode></xhtml:th>
                        </xhtml:tr>
                        <xhtml:tr>
                          <xhtml:td>yes</xhtml:td>
                          <xhtml:td>don't care</xhtml:td>
                          <xhtml:td>OS_IOCLOCKMODE_NONE</xhtml:td>
                        </xhtml:tr>
                        <xhtml:tr>
                          <xhtml:td>no</xhtml:td>
                          <xhtml:td>All writer and reader applications are located on the same core.</xhtml:td>
                          <xhtml:td>OS_IOCLOCKMODE_INTERRUPTS</xhtml:td>
                        </xhtml:tr>
                        <xhtml:tr>
                          <xhtml:td>no</xhtml:td>
                          <xhtml:td>All writer and reader applications are located on different cores.</xhtml:td>
                          <xhtml:td>OS_IOCLOCKMODE_SPINLOCKS</xhtml:td>
                        </xhtml:tr>
                        <xhtml:tr>
                          <xhtml:td>no</xhtml:td>
                          <xhtml:td>Some writer and/or reader applications are located on the same core, while others are located on different cores.</xhtml:td>
                          <xhtml:td>OS_IOCLOCKMODE_ALL</xhtml:td>
                        </xhtml:tr>
                      </xhtml:tbody>
                    </xhtml:table>
</xhtml:div>
</xhtml:div>
              </THE-VALUE>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-XHTML>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="SMI-889324">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-916bfa90513366b6033b4ebb05e88b13</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="SMI-FB8362E2-3F95-4C00-8CC5-7261A2EB41B3">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-f71c12daf9754c5c0ec9549bb0a19b12</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="RQM_SAFETY_MANUAL_ITEM">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-83df1902a3d82b5ad802413febd9486c</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-DATE THE-VALUE="2023-04-17T14:14:08.073-04:00">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-DATE-REF>id-aa6269f32be4c61f516adebdbf3b1e19</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-DATE-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-DATE>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-DATE THE-VALUE="2023-04-17T14:14:08.073-04:00">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-DATE-REF>id-1deeefdd91604feff8470574ac6fef3d</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-DATE-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-DATE>
          </VALUES>
          <TYPE>
            <SPEC-OBJECT-TYPE-REF>id-9005dd4fc53fa9c4b4bcb1b9bddbb116</SPEC-OBJECT-TYPE-REF>
          </TYPE>
        </SPEC-OBJECT>
        <SPEC-OBJECT IDENTIFIER="id-52902ef4b28603b3d96ac1a913549156" LAST-CHANGE="2023-04-17T14:14:08.073-04:00" LONG-NAME="c3e1bd6ee92186cfabe8accc82aa9ed8d84c7261ae0b971c80223795dbd9ca83">
          <VALUES>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="c3e1bd6ee92186cfabe8accc82aa9ed8d84c7261ae0b971c80223795dbd9ca83">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-474bf8df001703d4f13bcf6621ec60e3</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-XHTML>
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-XHTML-REF>id-356fa0b261512705956dc6124b01c001</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-XHTML-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
              <THE-VALUE>
                <xhtml:div>
<xhtml:div>
<xhtml:p>The user of MICROSAR Safe shall verify the consistency of the LockMode and the Spinlock pointer for all generated configuration structures of receivers on IOC communications. The configuration data structure of receivers in  Os_Ioc_Lcfg.c looks like:</xhtml:p>
<xhtml:pre>
<xhtml:code>CONST(Os_Ioc&lt;Bytes>ReceiveConfigType, OS_CONST)
<xhtml:br/>
OsCfg_IocRecv_&lt;NameOfIocCommunication> =
<xhtml:br/>
{
<xhtml:br/>
/* .Ioc      = */
<xhtml:br/>
{
<xhtml:br/>
/* .Base     = */
<xhtml:br/>
{
<xhtml:br/>
/* .Spinlock              = */ &lt;SpinlockPointer>,
<xhtml:br/>
/* .LockMode              = */ &lt;LockModeValue>,
<xhtml:br/>
...
<xhtml:br/>
/* .AccessingApplications = */ OS_APPID2MASK(&lt;NameOfOsApplication>)
<xhtml:br/>
},
<xhtml:br/>
...
<xhtml:br/>
},
<xhtml:br/>
...
<xhtml:br/>
};
<xhtml:br/>
</xhtml:code>
</xhtml:pre>
<xhtml:p>Where &lt;NameOfIocCommunication> is the configured short name of a container with definition ref: /MICROSAR/Os/OsIoc/OsIocCommunication. The value of &lt;Bytes> is one of: { 08, 16, 32, Ref }. The value &lt;NameOfOsApplication> is the short name of a configuration container, reffered to by the parameter: /MICROSAR/Os/OsIoc/OsIocCommunication/OsIocReceiverProperties/OsIocReceivingOsApplicationRef of the Ioc communication. The values at &lt;SpinlockPointer> and &lt;LockModeValue> shall be reviewed against the table for consistency:</xhtml:p>
<xhtml:table>
                      <xhtml:tbody>
                        <xhtml:tr>
                          <xhtml:th> &lt;LockModeValue> </xhtml:th>
                          <xhtml:th> &lt;SpinlockPointer> </xhtml:th>
                        </xhtml:tr>
                        <xhtml:tr>
                          <xhtml:td>OS_IOCLOCKMODE_NONE</xhtml:td>
                          <xhtml:td>NULL_PTR</xhtml:td>
                        </xhtml:tr>
                        <xhtml:tr>
                          <xhtml:td>OS_IOCLOCKMODE_INTERRUPTS</xhtml:td>
                          <xhtml:td>NULL_PTR</xhtml:td>
                        </xhtml:tr>
                        <xhtml:tr>
                          <xhtml:td>OS_IOCLOCKMODE_SPINLOCKS</xhtml:td>
                          <xhtml:td>&amp;OsCfg_Spinlock_IocSpinlock_&lt;NameOfIocCommunication></xhtml:td>
                        </xhtml:tr>
                        <xhtml:tr>
                          <xhtml:td>OS_IOCLOCKMODE_ALL</xhtml:td>
                          <xhtml:td>&amp;OsCfg_Spinlock_IocSpinlock_&lt;NameOfIocCommunication></xhtml:td>
                        </xhtml:tr>
                      </xhtml:tbody>
                    </xhtml:table>
</xhtml:div>
</xhtml:div>
              </THE-VALUE>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-XHTML>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="SMI-889325">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-916bfa90513366b6033b4ebb05e88b13</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="SMI-DB287ABF-2282-4377-BFE9-CA15DB3B5870">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-f71c12daf9754c5c0ec9549bb0a19b12</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="RQM_SAFETY_MANUAL_ITEM">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-83df1902a3d82b5ad802413febd9486c</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-DATE THE-VALUE="2023-04-17T14:14:08.073-04:00">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-DATE-REF>id-aa6269f32be4c61f516adebdbf3b1e19</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-DATE-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-DATE>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-DATE THE-VALUE="2023-04-17T14:14:08.073-04:00">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-DATE-REF>id-1deeefdd91604feff8470574ac6fef3d</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-DATE-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-DATE>
          </VALUES>
          <TYPE>
            <SPEC-OBJECT-TYPE-REF>id-9005dd4fc53fa9c4b4bcb1b9bddbb116</SPEC-OBJECT-TYPE-REF>
          </TYPE>
        </SPEC-OBJECT>
        <SPEC-OBJECT IDENTIFIER="id-0bbbf37d359688e8f8d732b79174d970" LAST-CHANGE="2023-04-17T14:14:08.073-04:00" LONG-NAME="5aa8c1ed66c25578e57f78a0347a154fa3f0e73ea554ef7c55e92cd48c26bdd5">
          <VALUES>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="5aa8c1ed66c25578e57f78a0347a154fa3f0e73ea554ef7c55e92cd48c26bdd5">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-474bf8df001703d4f13bcf6621ec60e3</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-XHTML>
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-XHTML-REF>id-356fa0b261512705956dc6124b01c001</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-XHTML-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
              <THE-VALUE>
                <xhtml:div>
<xhtml:div>
<xhtml:p>The user of MICROSAR Safe shall verify the consistency of the LockMode and the Spinlock pointer for all generated configuration structures of senders on IOC communications. The configuration structure of senders in Os_Ioc_Lcfg.c looks like:</xhtml:p>
<xhtml:pre>
<xhtml:code>CONST(Os_Ioc&lt;Bytes>SendConfigType, OS_CONST)
<xhtml:br/>
OsCfg_IocSend_&lt;NameOfIocCommunication>&lt;_&lt;OsIocSenderId>>? =
<xhtml:br/>
{
<xhtml:br/>
/* .Ioc       = */
<xhtml:br/>
{
<xhtml:br/>
/* .Base     = */
<xhtml:br/>
{
<xhtml:br/>
/* .Spinlock              = */ &lt;SpinlockPointer>,
<xhtml:br/>
/* .LockMode              = */ &lt;LockModeValue>,
<xhtml:br/>
...
<xhtml:br/>
/* .AccessingApplications = */ OS_APPID2MASK(&lt;NameOfOsApplication>)
<xhtml:br/>
},
<xhtml:br/>
...
<xhtml:br/>
},
<xhtml:br/>
/* .FifoWrite = */
<xhtml:br/>
{
<xhtml:br/>
...
<xhtml:br/>
/* .Data     = */ &lt;DataBufferPointer>,
<xhtml:br/>
...
<xhtml:br/>
}
<xhtml:br/>
};
<xhtml:br/>
</xhtml:code>
</xhtml:pre>
<xhtml:p>Where &lt;NameOfIocCommunication> is the configured short name of a container with definition ref: /MICROSAR/Os/OsIoc/OsIocCommunication and &lt;_&lt;OsIocSenderId>>? is the value of a parameter with definition ref: /MICROSAR/Os/OsIoc/OsIocCommunication/OsIocSenderProperties/OsIocSenderId of that IOC communication. This part of the name may not be available in 1:1 communication as the parameter needs not be configured then. The value of &lt;Bytes> is one of: { 08, 16, 32, Ref }. The value of &lt;NameOfOsApplication> is the short name of a configuration container, reffered to by the parameter: /MICROSAR/Os/OsIoc/OsIocCommunication/OsIocReceiverProperties/OsIocReceivingOsApplicationRef of the Ioc communication. The value of &lt;DataBufferPointer> will be OsCfg_Ioc_&lt;NameOfIocCommunication>&lt;_&lt;OsIocSenderId>>?_Buffer_Dyn, where the sender ID may not be identical to the one used for the name of the configuration structure. The values at &lt;SpinlockPointer> and &lt;LockModeValue> shall be reviewed against the table for consistency:</xhtml:p>
<xhtml:table>
                      <xhtml:tbody>
                        <xhtml:tr>
                          <xhtml:th> &lt;LockModeValue> </xhtml:th>
                          <xhtml:th> &lt;SpinlockPointer> </xhtml:th>
                        </xhtml:tr>
                        <xhtml:tr>
                          <xhtml:td>OS_IOCLOCKMODE_NONE</xhtml:td>
                          <xhtml:td>NULL_PTR</xhtml:td>
                        </xhtml:tr>
                        <xhtml:tr>
                          <xhtml:td>OS_IOCLOCKMODE_INTERRUPTS</xhtml:td>
                          <xhtml:td>NULL_PTR</xhtml:td>
                        </xhtml:tr>
                        <xhtml:tr>
                          <xhtml:td>OS_IOCLOCKMODE_SPINLOCKS</xhtml:td>
                          <xhtml:td>&amp;OsCfg_Spinlock_IocSpinlock_&lt;NameOfIocCommunication></xhtml:td>
                        </xhtml:tr>
                        <xhtml:tr>
                          <xhtml:td>OS_IOCLOCKMODE_ALL</xhtml:td>
                          <xhtml:td>&amp;OsCfg_Spinlock_IocSpinlock_&lt;NameOfIocCommunication></xhtml:td>
                        </xhtml:tr>
                      </xhtml:tbody>
                    </xhtml:table>
</xhtml:div>
</xhtml:div>
              </THE-VALUE>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-XHTML>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="SMI-889326">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-916bfa90513366b6033b4ebb05e88b13</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="SMI-5C94DB88-4595-4A66-AFD8-800AE0D1CE88">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-f71c12daf9754c5c0ec9549bb0a19b12</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="RQM_SAFETY_MANUAL_ITEM">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-83df1902a3d82b5ad802413febd9486c</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-DATE THE-VALUE="2023-04-17T14:14:08.073-04:00">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-DATE-REF>id-aa6269f32be4c61f516adebdbf3b1e19</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-DATE-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-DATE>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-DATE THE-VALUE="2023-04-17T14:14:08.073-04:00">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-DATE-REF>id-1deeefdd91604feff8470574ac6fef3d</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-DATE-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-DATE>
          </VALUES>
          <TYPE>
            <SPEC-OBJECT-TYPE-REF>id-9005dd4fc53fa9c4b4bcb1b9bddbb116</SPEC-OBJECT-TYPE-REF>
          </TYPE>
        </SPEC-OBJECT>
        <SPEC-OBJECT IDENTIFIER="id-fb052ab65a683f2aa4fbad80e79ef7bf" LAST-CHANGE="2023-04-17T14:14:08.073-04:00" LONG-NAME="a68737d9140677034af8d18ae56764ffe1ea2651bbbb264a70607d34bdc8ea97">
          <VALUES>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="a68737d9140677034af8d18ae56764ffe1ea2651bbbb264a70607d34bdc8ea97">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-474bf8df001703d4f13bcf6621ec60e3</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-XHTML>
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-XHTML-REF>id-356fa0b261512705956dc6124b01c001</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-XHTML-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
              <THE-VALUE>
                <xhtml:div>
<xhtml:div>
<xhtml:p>The user of MICROSAR Safe shall verify the correct generation of the LockMode for all senders of a specific IOC communication. See SMI-889326 for the relevant configuration structures. The value for &lt;LockMode> shall be identical for all senders and be in accordance to the table:</xhtml:p>
<xhtml:table>
                      <xhtml:tbody>
                        <xhtml:tr>
                          <xhtml:th>More than one sender</xhtml:th>
                          <xhtml:th>&lt;DataBufferPointer></xhtml:th>
                          <xhtml:th>Core local and/or Cross-Core communication</xhtml:th>
                          <xhtml:th>&lt;LockModeValue></xhtml:th>
                        </xhtml:tr>
                        <xhtml:tr>
                          <xhtml:td>no</xhtml:td>
                          <xhtml:td>not relevant</xhtml:td>
                          <xhtml:td>not relevant</xhtml:td>
                          <xhtml:td>OS_IOCLOCKMODE_NONE</xhtml:td>
                        </xhtml:tr>
                        <xhtml:tr>
                          <xhtml:td>yes</xhtml:td>
                          <xhtml:td>different for all senders</xhtml:td>
                          <xhtml:td>not relevant</xhtml:td>
                          <xhtml:td>OS_IOCLOCKMODE_NONE</xhtml:td>
                        </xhtml:tr>
                        <xhtml:tr>
                          <xhtml:td>yes</xhtml:td>
                          <xhtml:td>Identical for all senders (typically named with lowest sender ID)</xhtml:td>
                          <xhtml:td>All sender applications are located on the same core.</xhtml:td>
                          <xhtml:td>OS_IOCLOCKMODE_INTERRUPTS</xhtml:td>
                        </xhtml:tr>
                        <xhtml:tr>
                          <xhtml:td>yes</xhtml:td>
                          <xhtml:td>Identical for all senders (typically named with lowest sender ID)</xhtml:td>
                          <xhtml:td>All sender applications are located on diferent cores.</xhtml:td>
                          <xhtml:td>OS_IOCLOCKMODE_SPINLOCKS</xhtml:td>
                        </xhtml:tr>
                        <xhtml:tr>
                          <xhtml:td>yes</xhtml:td>
                          <xhtml:td>Identical for all senders (typically named with lowest sender ID)</xhtml:td>
                          <xhtml:td>Some sender applications are located on the same core while others are located on different core.</xhtml:td>
                          <xhtml:td>OS_IOCLOCKMODE_ALL</xhtml:td>
                        </xhtml:tr>
                      </xhtml:tbody>
                    </xhtml:table>
<xhtml:p>Mind that MICROSAR-OS uses the same data pointer for all sender applications when a receiver callback is configured.</xhtml:p>
</xhtml:div>
</xhtml:div>
              </THE-VALUE>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-XHTML>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="SMI-889327">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-916bfa90513366b6033b4ebb05e88b13</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="SMI-D386C82B-5B77-4C12-B425-68ACCB2268C1">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-f71c12daf9754c5c0ec9549bb0a19b12</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="RQM_SAFETY_MANUAL_ITEM">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-83df1902a3d82b5ad802413febd9486c</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-DATE THE-VALUE="2023-04-17T14:14:08.073-04:00">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-DATE-REF>id-aa6269f32be4c61f516adebdbf3b1e19</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-DATE-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-DATE>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-DATE THE-VALUE="2023-04-17T14:14:08.073-04:00">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-DATE-REF>id-1deeefdd91604feff8470574ac6fef3d</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-DATE-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-DATE>
          </VALUES>
          <TYPE>
            <SPEC-OBJECT-TYPE-REF>id-9005dd4fc53fa9c4b4bcb1b9bddbb116</SPEC-OBJECT-TYPE-REF>
          </TYPE>
        </SPEC-OBJECT>
        <SPEC-OBJECT IDENTIFIER="id-b3bdb9f0dac04d214b38c80698488178" LAST-CHANGE="2023-04-17T14:14:08.073-04:00" LONG-NAME="ed0904f705e305ca690bddc785c28a6b2c75978da402010392f44b476a0bd04a">
          <VALUES>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="ed0904f705e305ca690bddc785c28a6b2c75978da402010392f44b476a0bd04a">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-474bf8df001703d4f13bcf6621ec60e3</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-XHTML>
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-XHTML-REF>id-cccf5234afd68596b1e3e3f55dea2015</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-XHTML-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
              <THE-VALUE>
                <xhtml:div>
<xhtml:div>
<xhtml:p>Safety requirements required from other components</xhtml:p>
</xhtml:div>
</xhtml:div>
              </THE-VALUE>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-XHTML>
