        <SPEC-OBJECT IDENTIFIER="id-9b2507d442cf915541dc52fa9d27aba3" LAST-CHANGE="2023-04-17T14:14:08.073-04:00" LONG-NAME="c5596e32769a0180af89e7a6d5d729556e527b00efa43aab674ce4a8ee7512d2">
          <VALUES>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="c5596e32769a0180af89e7a6d5d729556e527b00efa43aab674ce4a8ee7512d2">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-474bf8df001703d4f13bcf6621ec60e3</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-XHTML>
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-XHTML-REF>id-356fa0b261512705956dc6124b01c001</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-XHTML-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
              <THE-VALUE>
                <xhtml:div>
<xhtml:div>
<xhtml:p>
The user of MICROSAR Safe shall verify that the array Core2Thread in the object OsCfg_Hal_Core2Thread contains all physical cores.
<xhtml:br/>
For each existing physical hardware core identifier there shall be one corresponding entry inside the array which is indexed by the physical hardware core identifier provided directly by the hardware registers.
</xhtml:p>
</xhtml:div>
</xhtml:div>
              </THE-VALUE>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-XHTML>
