        <SPEC-OBJECT IDENTIFIER="id-ab0e27402b27b1c7b0f110dd08f48307" LAST-CHANGE="2023-04-17T14:14:08.073-04:00" LONG-NAME="f2d9b462b2bba460db67ee71f43e91c19b94def48e83edf1829e2e5e09070165">
          <VALUES>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="f2d9b462b2bba460db67ee71f43e91c19b94def48e83edf1829e2e5e09070165">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-474bf8df001703d4f13bcf6621ec60e3</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-XHTML>
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-XHTML-REF>id-356fa0b261512705956dc6124b01c001</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-XHTML-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
              <THE-VALUE>
                <xhtml:div>
<xhtml:div>
<xhtml:p>
The user of MICROSAR Safe shall verify that the following configuration struct is generated into Os_Hal_Timer_Lcfg.c if the FTM timer is used by the OS:
<xhtml:br/>
CONST(Os_Hal_TimerFrtConfigType, OS_CONST) OsCfg_Hal_TimerFrt_&lt;CounterName>
<xhtml:br/>
The following struct members must be checked (where &lt;X> (0, 2, 4, 6) is the channel ID) and &lt;y> is the timer module):
<xhtml:br/>
ModuleControlRegisterAddress  = OS_HAL_TIMER_FTM&lt;Y>_BASE
<xhtml:br/>
ModuleCountRegisterAddress    = OS_HAL_TIMER_FTM&lt;Y>_BASE + OS_HAL_TIMER_FTM_COUNTREGISTER_OFFSET
<xhtml:br/>
ChannelControlRegisterAddress = OS_HAL_TIMER_FTM&lt;Y>_BASE + OS_HAL_TIMER_FTM_CHANNEL&lt;X>_OFFSET
<xhtml:br/>
ChannelCompareRegisterAddress = OS_HAL_TIMER_FTM&lt;Y>_BASE + OS_HAL_TIMER_FTM_CHANNEL&lt;X>_OFFSET + OS_HAL_TIMER_FTM_CHANNEL_CMP_OFFSET
</xhtml:p>
</xhtml:div>
</xhtml:div>
              </THE-VALUE>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-XHTML>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="SMI-333241">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-916bfa90513366b6033b4ebb05e88b13</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING>
