        <SPEC-OBJECT IDENTIFIER="id-d67e71abab2396adbf3409bbae269fe2" LAST-CHANGE="2023-04-17T14:14:08.073-04:00" LONG-NAME="9e841ad4d643a96cabb33a008e785a7656026484f914e5e995cc560e304e25b9">
          <VALUES>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="9e841ad4d643a96cabb33a008e785a7656026484f914e5e995cc560e304e25b9">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-474bf8df001703d4f13bcf6621ec60e3</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-XHTML>
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-XHTML-REF>id-356fa0b261512705956dc6124b01c001</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-XHTML-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
              <THE-VALUE>
                <xhtml:div>
<xhtml:div>
<xhtml:p>
The user of MICROSAR Safe shall verify for all non-autostarted Autosar cores that the generated value of CoreStartAddress has to be the base address of the interrupt vector table of the corresponding core.
<xhtml:br/>
The struct &quot;OsCfg_Hal_Core_OsCoreX&quot; shall be checked (where &lt;X> is the logical core ID of the checked core)
<xhtml:br/>
CONST(Os_Hal_CoreConfigType, OS_CONST) OsCfg_Hal_Core_OsCoreX = {
<xhtml:br/>
/* .CoreId  = */ X,
<xhtml:br/>
/* .CoreStartAddress = */ (uint32)(&amp;OsCfg_Hal_Core_OsCoreX_VectorTable)
<xhtml:br/>
};
</xhtml:p>
</xhtml:div>
</xhtml:div>
