            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-XHTML>
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-XHTML-REF>id-356fa0b261512705956dc6124b01c001</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-XHTML-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
              <THE-VALUE>
                <xhtml:div>
<xhtml:div>
<xhtml:p>
The user of MICROSAR Safe shall verify that the following configuration struct is generated into Os_Hal_Timer_Lcfg.c if the TCPWM0 timer is used by the OS:
<xhtml:br/>
CONST(Os_Hal_TimerFrtConfigType, OS_CONST) OsCfg_Hal_TimerFrt_&lt;CounterName>
<xhtml:br/>
The following struct members must be checked (where &lt;X> is the channel ID):
<xhtml:br/>
TimerBaseAddr = OS_HAL_TIMER_FRT_TCPWM0_GROUP2_BASE
<xhtml:br/>
CounterIndex = OS_HAL_TCPWM_COUNTER_X
</xhtml:p>
</xhtml:div>
</xhtml:div>
              </THE-VALUE>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-XHTML>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="SMI-568210">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-916bfa90513366b6033b4ebb05e88b13</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
