        <SPEC-OBJECT IDENTIFIER="id-52d9bae511844a5290774350e450a52e" LAST-CHANGE="2023-04-17T14:14:08.073-04:00" LONG-NAME="92f2d39cd9260e708697ae6d59c252a266ed15431f9b4d0b53c8f3bc19f789c0">
          <VALUES>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="92f2d39cd9260e708697ae6d59c252a266ed15431f9b4d0b53c8f3bc19f789c0">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-474bf8df001703d4f13bcf6621ec60e3</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-XHTML>
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-XHTML-REF>id-356fa0b261512705956dc6124b01c001</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-XHTML-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
              <THE-VALUE>
                <xhtml:div>
<xhtml:div>
<xhtml:p>
<xhtml:strong>The user of MICROSAR Safe shall ensure that all connected SWCs expect the same converted data.</xhtml:strong>
</xhtml:p>
<xhtml:p>The RTE offers conversions that can be applied to specific connections.</xhtml:p>
<xhtml:p>Vector recommends not using data conversion for safety-related connections.</xhtml:p>
<xhtml:p>Verification can e.g. be performed by review or integration testing of all data conversions.</xhtml:p>
<xhtml:p>The RTE Analyzer lists all APIs of SWCs that perform data conversion to assist in this integration step.</xhtml:p>
</xhtml:div>
</xhtml:div>
              </THE-VALUE>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-XHTML>
