        <SPEC-OBJECT IDENTIFIER="id-6fb2a6fe4eeb49ea307ec4fa7351181c" LAST-CHANGE="2023-04-17T14:14:08.073-04:00" LONG-NAME="415ed98f5cccca1e2482b6360c699e013608f2f57e0a38247710a1ed75578bb5">
          <VALUES>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="415ed98f5cccca1e2482b6360c699e013608f2f57e0a38247710a1ed75578bb5">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-474bf8df001703d4f13bcf6621ec60e3</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-XHTML>
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-XHTML-REF>id-356fa0b261512705956dc6124b01c001</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-XHTML-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
              <THE-VALUE>
                <xhtml:div>
<xhtml:div>
<xhtml:p>
The user of MICROSAR Safe shall verify that the Wdg driver services are only called by the watchdog interface.
<xhtml:br/>
This requierment does not apply to the service for initalization and the interface to Gpt (general purpose timer).
<xhtml:br/>
This requirement is fulfilled for all components of MICROSAR.
<xhtml:br/>
If e.g. the trigger condition is extended by another component, this may lead to unintended triggering of the watchdog.
</xhtml:p>
</xhtml:div>
</xhtml:div>
              </THE-VALUE>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-XHTML>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="SMI-254">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-916bfa90513366b6033b4ebb05e88b13</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
