        <SPEC-OBJECT IDENTIFIER="id-0cc080a57a99afcdd63e850584b0a8a4" LAST-CHANGE="2023-04-17T14:14:08.073-04:00" LONG-NAME="d1d2f083bdda7f0f7a9694821e78816983b87251edef06e480a6559611dc66da">
          <VALUES>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="d1d2f083bdda7f0f7a9694821e78816983b87251edef06e480a6559611dc66da">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-474bf8df001703d4f13bcf6621ec60e3</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-XHTML>
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-XHTML-REF>id-356fa0b261512705956dc6124b01c001</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-XHTML-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
              <THE-VALUE>
                <xhtml:div>
<xhtml:div>
<xhtml:p>
The Wdg interface shall call the service to set the mode and the trigger condition as expected by the Wdg driver.
<xhtml:br/>
This requirement is fulfilled if the watchdog interface and manager by Vector is used.
<xhtml:br/>
If the watchdog is not properly set up, it may not provide the expected protection.
</xhtml:p>
</xhtml:div>
</xhtml:div>
              </THE-VALUE>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-XHTML>
