        <SPEC-OBJECT IDENTIFIER="id-505763fa45226baeaee9b85a160f7ee4" LAST-CHANGE="2023-04-17T14:14:08.073-04:00" LONG-NAME="c18084f43fc9af85b002778226565ef1aeb21fcae8983c62fa2605da618d3df2">
          <VALUES>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="c18084f43fc9af85b002778226565ef1aeb21fcae8983c62fa2605da618d3df2">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-474bf8df001703d4f13bcf6621ec60e3</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-XHTML>
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-XHTML-REF>id-356fa0b261512705956dc6124b01c001</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-XHTML-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
              <THE-VALUE>
                <xhtml:div>
<xhtml:div>
<xhtml:p>
The user of MICROSAR Safe shall set the value of <xhtml:em>WdgMTimebaseSource</xhtml:em> according to the required source of time ticks:
</xhtml:p>
<xhtml:table>
                      <xhtml:tbody>
                        <xhtml:tr>
                          <xhtml:th> WdgMTimebaseSource </xhtml:th>
                          <xhtml:th> Description </xhtml:th>
                        </xhtml:tr>
                        <xhtml:tr>
                          <xhtml:td> WDGM_INTERNAL_SOFTWARE_TICK </xhtml:td>
                          <xhtml:td> An internal time source for Deadline Monitoring is selected. The tick counter is incremented each time the <xhtml:em>WdgM_MainFunction()</xhtml:em> is invoked.</xhtml:td>
                        </xhtml:tr>
                        <xhtml:tr>
                          <xhtml:td> WDGM_OS_COUNTER_TICK </xhtml:td>
                          <xhtml:td> An OsCounter is selected for Deadline Monitoring as timebase.  The user of MICROSAR Safe is responsible for configuring the OsCounter accurately.</xhtml:td>
                        </xhtml:tr>
                        <xhtml:tr>
                          <xhtml:td> WDGM_EXTERNAL_TICK </xhtml:td>
                          <xhtml:td> An external time source for Deadline Monitoring is selected. The tick counter is incremented each time the <xhtml:em>WdgM_UpdateTickCount()</xhtml:em> function is invoked. The function is implemented in the WdgM. The user of MICROSAR Safe is responsible for calling WdgM_UpdateTickCount() accurately.</xhtml:td>
                        </xhtml:tr>
                      </xhtml:tbody>
                    </xhtml:table>
<xhtml:p>This requirement is necessary to ensure usage in a released configuration.</xhtml:p>
</xhtml:div>
</xhtml:div>
              </THE-VALUE>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-XHTML>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="SMI-498">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-916bfa90513366b6033b4ebb05e88b13</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING>
