        <SPEC-OBJECT IDENTIFIER="id-c222c465a6c44d277cf57e7543d15fd0" LAST-CHANGE="2023-04-17T14:14:08.073-04:00" LONG-NAME="3e197e1e356dd7f618a32108c475f10fe1cb12b11d0dbe5c3f5f519d14f35a6e">
          <VALUES>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="3e197e1e356dd7f618a32108c475f10fe1cb12b11d0dbe5c3f5f519d14f35a6e">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-474bf8df001703d4f13bcf6621ec60e3</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-XHTML>
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-XHTML-REF>id-356fa0b261512705956dc6124b01c001</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-XHTML-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
              <THE-VALUE>
                <xhtml:div>
<xhtml:div>
<xhtml:p>
The user of MICROSAR Safe shall verify that for the following arrays in <xhtml:em>WdgM_Cfg.c</xhtml:em>, the array length matches the number of items in the array:
</xhtml:p>
<xhtml:ul>
                      <xhtml:li>
<xhtml:em>WdgMTransition</xhtml:em>
</xhtml:li>
                      <xhtml:li>
<xhtml:em>WdgMGlobalTransition</xhtml:em>
</xhtml:li>
                      <xhtml:li>
all arrays named <xhtml:em>StartsGlobalTransition</xhtml:em>&lt;se>_&lt;cp>_&lt;i>_ (for a supervised entity se, a checkpoint cp and an integer i)
</xhtml:li>
                      <xhtml:li>
<xhtml:em>WdgMCheckPoint</xhtml:em>
</xhtml:li>
                      <xhtml:li>
<xhtml:em>WdgMSupervisedEntity</xhtml:em>
</xhtml:li>
                      <xhtml:li>
all arrays named <xhtml:em>WdgMTriggerMode_core&lt;ID></xhtml:em> (for each core with ID)
</xhtml:li>
                      <xhtml:li>
<xhtml:em>WdgMWatchdogDevice&lt;ID></xhtml:em> (for each core with ID)
</xhtml:li>
                      <xhtml:li>
<xhtml:em>WdgMAllowedCallers</xhtml:em>
</xhtml:li>
                    </xhtml:ul>
<xhtml:p>
Some of these arrays have preprocessor defines for their size, e.g. <xhtml:em>WdgMCheckPoint [WDGM_NR_OF_CHECKPOINTS]</xhtml:em>. These defines can be found in <xhtml:em>WdgM_Cfg.h</xhtml:em>.
</xhtml:p>
</xhtml:div>
</xhtml:div>
              </THE-VALUE>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-XHTML>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="SMI-506">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-916bfa90513366b6033b4ebb05e88b13</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="SMI-B0C19999-07EE-49DD-9DD9-8951942E7357">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-f71c12daf9754c5c0ec9549bb0a19b12</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING>
