        <SPEC-OBJECT IDENTIFIER="id-ca33033fb4d551f08cf1de2d30263559" LAST-CHANGE="2023-04-17T14:14:08.073-04:00" LONG-NAME="158f515288e5637f8d9b37f0fcd285317d70096aae28516fa26db1988443e4d3">
          <VALUES>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="158f515288e5637f8d9b37f0fcd285317d70096aae28516fa26db1988443e4d3">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-474bf8df001703d4f13bcf6621ec60e3</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-XHTML>
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-XHTML-REF>id-356fa0b261512705956dc6124b01c001</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-XHTML-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
              <THE-VALUE>
                <xhtml:div>
<xhtml:div>
<xhtml:p>
The user of MICROSAR Safe shall verify that each item in the array <xhtml:em>WdgMSupervisedEntity</xhtml:em> follows the rule:
</xhtml:p>
<xhtml:ul>
                      <xhtml:li>
<xhtml:em>WdgMCheckpointRef</xhtml:em> has a value of the form _&amp;WdgMCheckPoint[<xhtml:a>i</xhtml:a>] with i &lt; WDGM_NR_OF_CHECKPOINTS, and
</xhtml:li>
                    </xhtml:ul>
<xhtml:p>
The array can be found in <xhtml:em>WdgM_Cfg.c</xhtml:em>.
</xhtml:p>
</xhtml:div>
</xhtml:div>
              </THE-VALUE>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-XHTML>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="SMI-507">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-916bfa90513366b6033b4ebb05e88b13</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING>
