        <SPEC-OBJECT IDENTIFIER="id-a24ec52cc397b4e34dcd8dd99a9e747a" LAST-CHANGE="2023-04-17T14:14:08.073-04:00" LONG-NAME="38d559880a6fef239143b662d46d007504393c641d48979baf481517017a0a0c">
          <VALUES>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="38d559880a6fef239143b662d46d007504393c641d48979baf481517017a0a0c">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-474bf8df001703d4f13bcf6621ec60e3</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-XHTML>
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-XHTML-REF>id-356fa0b261512705956dc6124b01c001</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-XHTML-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
              <THE-VALUE>
                <xhtml:div>
<xhtml:div>
<xhtml:p>
The user of MICROSAR Safe shall verify that each WdgM_StatusReportToRte member of struct WdgM_ConfigType and each WdgM_StatusReportToRte member of struct WdgM_SupervisedEntityType has a valid entry if WDGM_STATUS_REPORTING_MECHANISM is set to WDGM_USE_MODE_SWITCH_PORTS.
<xhtml:br/>
The functions must be implemented by the Rte and must have the following signature: Std_ReturnType (*WdgM_StatusReportToRte) (WdgMMode).
<xhtml:br/>
Both structs can be found in WdgM_Cfg.c.
</xhtml:p>
</xhtml:div>
</xhtml:div>
              </THE-VALUE>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-XHTML>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="SMI-27923">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>id-916bfa90513366b6033b4ebb05e88b13</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING>
